extends ../../docs-template-partials/_docs-article

block prepend article
  - var sectionId = "basic-buttons"
  - var sectionTitle = "Buttons"

block section
  p.
    Button classes can be applied to button tags, input-button tags and hyperlink anchor tags:

  p
    <button class="btn" type="submit">Button</button> #[code .btn]

  p.
    #[a(href="#/").btn Hyperlink] #[code .btn]

  p
    <input class="btn" value="Input" type="submit"> #[code .btn]

  p Block width button: #[code .btn.btn--block]

  p
    button.btn.btn--block Block width button

  h3  Button Colors
  
  p
    button.btn Default
    |  #[code .btn]
  p
    button.btn.btn--primary Primary
    |  #[code .btn.btn--primary]
  p
    button.btn.btn--secondary Secondary
    |  #[code .btn.btn--secondary]
  p
    button.btn.btn--warning Warning
    |  #[code .btn.btn--warning]
  p
    button.btn.btn--success Success
    |  #[code .btn.btn--success]
  p
    button.btn.btn--danger Danger
    |  #[code .btn.btn--danger]

  h3 Button States

  p.
    #[code .btn--active] #[code .btn--disabled]
  p
    button.btn Default
    button.btn.btn--active Default active
    button.btn.btn--disabled(aria-disabled="true") Default disabled
  p
    button.btn.btn--primary Primary
    button.btn.btn--primary.btn--active Primary active
    button.btn.btn--primary.btn--disabled(aria-disabled="true") Primary disabled
  p
    button.btn.btn--secondary Secondary
    button.btn.btn--secondary.btn--active Secondary active
    button.btn.btn--secondary.btn--disabled(aria-disabled="true") Secondary disabled
  p
    button.btn.btn--warning Warning
    button.btn.btn--warning.btn--active Warning active
    button.btn.btn--warning.btn--disabled(aria-disabled="true") Warning disabled
  p
    button.btn.btn--success Success
    button.btn.btn--success.btn--active Success active
    button.btn.btn--success.btn--disabled(aria-disabled="true") Success disabled
  p
    button.btn.btn--danger Danger
    button.btn.btn--danger.btn--active Danger active
    button.btn.btn--danger.btn--disabled(aria-disabled="true") Danger disabled
  
  p The active and disabled state classes also work for outline buttons and 3D buttons (see below).
  
  h3 Outline Buttons
  
  p #[code .btn--outline]
  
  p
    button.btn.btn--outline Default
    button.btn.btn--primary.btn--outline Primary
    button.btn.btn--secondary.btn--outline Secondary
    button.btn.btn--warning.btn--outline Warning
    button.btn.btn--success.btn--outline Success
    button.btn.btn--danger.btn--outline Danger

  h3 3D Buttons

  p.
    By default, Codebase has flat buttons. If you override the variable #[code $btn--3d: false !default] to #[code true] then all buttons (except outlines) will be made to appear as 3D using gloss and shadow gradients (as you see in the examples below).

  p.
    However, in default mode you can also add class #[code .btn--3d] to any button (except outlines) to make it 3D.

  p
    button.btn.btn--3d Default
    button.btn.btn--primary.btn--3d Primary
    button.btn.btn--secondary.btn--3d Secondary
    button.btn.btn--warning.btn--3d Warning
    button.btn.btn--success.btn--3d Success
    button.btn.btn--danger.btn--3d Danger  

  p Add #[code .btn--big-text] for increased text and/or icon size:
  
  a.btn.btn--primary(href="#/")
    | Find out more &hellip;
  =" "
  a.btn.btn--primary.btn--big-text(href="#/")
    | Find out more &hellip;
  
  h3.mt--line Small, Default and Large Buttons
  
  p Add #[code .btn--sm] for a smaller button, or #[code .btn--lg] for a larger button:

  a.btn.btn--primary.btn--sm(href="#/")
    | Smaller
  = " "
  a.btn.btn--primary(href="#/")
    | Default
  = " "
  a.btn.btn--primary.btn--lg(href="#/")
    | Larger

  p.mt--line.text--initial-icon.b--thin.b--green-lighten-1.b--rounded.p--16.pl--80.bg--green-lighten-3
    i.fa.fa-info-circle.text--green-darken-1
    | The smaller form button size has been designed for fitting within menus and menubars. In that context, give it a margin class #[code .m--4] to position it correctly.

  h3 Buttons with Big Text and/or Big Icon

  p Button sizes can be used in combination with #[code .btn--big-text] (for increased text and/or icon size) and #[code .btn--outline]:  
  
