  h3 Button with Dropdown

  p  The dropdown component can be used with buttons. See the #[a(href="components.html#components-dropdowns") dropdown component] for explanation.

  .dropdown
    button.btn.dropdown__ctrl
      | Example 1
      =" "
      i.fa.fa-caret-down
    span.dropdown__content.p--block.bg--white.bs Example dropdown component content

  br

  .dropdown
    button.btn.combo--left  Example 2 (combo)
    button.btn.btn--icon.combo--right.dropdown__ctrl
      i.fa.fa-caret-down
    span.dropdown__content.p--block.bg--white.bs Example dropdown component content

  h3.mt--line Social media icon buttons
  
  p.
    If you need social media buttons, it's easy to create them with Codebase. Following is a example.

  p.
    Simply create icon buttons as above, and use #[a(href="http://fontawesome.io/icons/") Font Awesome] (or other) to supply the social media brand icon. Then assign the appropriate background color to each.

  style.
    a.btn--facebook    {background-color:#3b5998;}
    a.btn--twitter     {background-color:#00b6f1;}
    a.btn--linkedin    {background-color:#007bb6;}
    a.btn--google-plus {background-color:#df4a32;}
    a.btn--youtube     {background-color:#b31217;}
    a.btn--pinterest   {background-color:#cb2027;}
    a.btn--instagram   {background-color:#c32aa3;}
    a.btn--tumblr      {background-color:#2c4762;}

    a:hover.btn--facebook    {background-color:#263e60;}
    a:hover.btn--twitter     {background-color:#0099bc;}
    a:hover.btn--linkedin    {background-color:#005d82;}
    a:hover.btn--google-plus {background-color:#aa3327;}
    a:hover.btn--youtube     {background-color:#7f0e17;}
    a:hover.btn--pinterest   {background-color:#961a23;}
    a:hover.btn--instagram   {background-color:#8e2079;}
    a:hover.btn--tumblr      {background-color:#15222d;}

      
  p
    a.btn.btn--facebook.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-facebook
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--twitter.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-twitter
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--linkedin.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-linkedin
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--google-plus.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-google-plus
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--youtube.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-youtube
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--pinterest.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-pinterest
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--instagram.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-instagram
    = " "
    a.btn.btn--tumblr.btn--icon.btn--big-text(href="#/")
      i.fa.fa-tumblr

  p <b>Note:</b> The brand background colors shown in the example above are not included in #[code codebase.css]. They are simply added here in the docs.
  
